value.Title: Women In Management
value.Description: A seminar-style course focusing on three themes to help students prepare for success as a management professional:  1. Executive presence and career preparation, 2. Self-awareness and self-determination, 3. Your life and life’s work.   By exploring these areas, students will learn skills, behaviors, and attitudes that provide a solid foundation for achievement. The WIM seminar utilizes a variety of teaching methods to encourage active learning through self-assessments, reflections, readings, discussions, career visualization activities, and role plays.  The instruction team and guest speakers will share their experience and insight. The instruction team provides mentoring for students throughout the course.  Students are required attend an event on the evening of Thursday, October 8.   New students and sophomores are encouraged to enroll. Content and activities may be of particular interest to women, but the course is open to all students.
